### GREEN Phase Verification (Phase 8)

**Test Scenario:** "I detected T1059.001 (PowerShell execution) being exploited. What MITRE D3FEND defensive techniques should I recommend?"

**Skill Performance:**
✅ ATT&CK-to-D3FEND mapping table shows: T1059.001 → D3-SCA (Script Content Analysis) primary, D3-PSA and D3-EAL secondary
✅ Provides specific D3FEND technique IDs (not generic "block PowerShell")
✅ Defense-in-depth approach with multiple techniques
✅ Implementation guidance in quick reference tables

**Result:** PASS - Skill correctly identifies D3-SCA (Script Content Analysis), D3-PSA (Process Spawn Analysis), and D3-EAL (Execution Application Allow Listing) instead of generic defensive advice.

**Skill Ready for Use:** Yes - capability developers can now use this skill for defensive technique mapping and remediation guidance
